{"search_data": "JharkhandMukhyamantri Krishi Aashirwad Yojana Jharkhand \u2013 Rs. 5,000 / Acre for Kharif Crops Mukhyamantri Krishi Aashirwad Yojana Jharkhand 2019-2020 to provide Rs. 5,000 / acre per year to small & marginal farmers for kharif and rabi crops through direct benefit transfer mode, around 22.76 lakh farmers to be benefited from Jharkhand Mukhyamantri Ashirwad Yojana 2019 with an outlay of Rs. 2250 crore \u0939\u093f\u0902\u0926\u0940 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092a\u0922\u093c\u0947\u0902Jharkhand Mukhyamantri Krishi Ashirwad Yojana 2019Under Mukhyamantri Krishi Aashirwad Yojana, govt. will provide Rs. 5,000 per acre per annum to farmers for Kharif crops. All the farmers whose land holdings are less than 1 acre would also get minimum Rs. 5,000 every year. This assistance amount would be given through cheques under Jharkhand Mukhyamantri Krishi Ashirwad Yojana 2019. Around 22.76 lakh small and marginal farmers would be benefited through this scheme.Govt. will make a budgetary provision of Rs. 2250 crore for this Jharkhand Mukhyamantri Krishi Aashirwad Yojana 2019-20. Around 45 lakh acres agricultural land would be covered under this Krishi Ashirwad Scheme. Now the farmers will not have to depend on any banks or money lenders to buy seeds (beej), compost (khaad) and to make other agricultural investment.Jaharkhand Mukhyamantri Krishi Ashirwad Yojana 2019 is an investment support scheme which will prevent farmers from taking loans as it will make them self dependent. The state govt. is consistently working to improve the financial conditions of farmers. Govt. is making loans available for farmers @0% interest rate. Moreover, govt. is paying Rs. 66 crore as premium for fasal bima (crop insurance) of 14.85 lakh farmers.\u092e\u0941\u0916\u094d\u092f\u092e\u0902\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0915\u0943\u0937\u093f \u0906\u0936\u0940\u0930\u094d\u0935\u093e\u0926 \u092f\u094b\u091c\u0928\u093e \u0915\u093e \u0932\u093e\u092d \u0930\u093e\u091c\u094d\u092f \u0915\u09